22:28.723 --> 22:30.338
It's his choice.

22:30.433 --> 22:34.221
If he does more treatments,
he could live longer.

22:34.312 --> 22:36.268
A year, maybe two.

22:36.356 --> 22:38.472
lwork in the health industry, Del. I've seen...

22:38.566 --> 22:41.273
-Miracles?
-Call it what you will.

22:41.361 --> 22:44.444
I've seen people live longer
than what their doctors said they would.

22:45.156 --> 22:46.862
Doc Powell's a realist.

22:46.950 --> 22:49.692
Basically, he told our father
chemo's no longer a viable option.

22:49.786 --> 22:52.323
-That tells me something.
-Tells you what?

22:53.331 --> 22:55.617
-To give up hope?
-No.

22:56.292 --> 22:58.999
It says to me that we should
start preparing for what's inevitable.

23:01.256 --> 23:03.622
He's gonna die, Delmond.

23:03.716 --> 23:06.628
We all got to deal with that in our own way.

23:07.136 --> 23:09.798
I'm gonna honor Daddy's wishes.
I'm hoping you will, too.

23:12.183 --> 23:13.514
(SNIFFLES)

23:19.232 --> 23:21.689
(SOUL MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

23:23.194 --> 23:27.153
-LaDONNA: Morning, big papa.
-Morning to you, beautiful.

23:27.240 --> 23:31.199
-You in that old stuff mood today.
-Just in a mood.

23:31.286 --> 23:36.121
Gary Walker and The Boogie Kings.
Tommy McLain wrote that one.

23:36.207 --> 23:39.791
McLain come out of Jonesville, Louisiana.
He did that swamp pop thing.

23:39.877 --> 23:42.334
I wouldn't know. ljust like it, that's all.

23:42.422 --> 23:44.913
-You want some juice?
-No, I'm good.

23:45.592 --> 23:47.378
-(WORKER HAMMERING)
-How much they overcharging you for?

23:49.137 --> 23:50.673
Bringing the wiring up to code.

23:50.763 --> 23:52.845
I had to do that to get my permits.

23:52.932 --> 23:54.388
That's gonna cost you now.

23:54.475 --> 23:57.763
But if you ever decide to sell this place,
you'll be ready.

23:57.854 --> 23:59.845
I know, you ain't never gonna sell.

23:59.939 --> 24:01.179
You got that right.

24:01.733 --> 24:03.348
It's for my boys.

24:04.861 --> 24:08.445
I got a steadyjob now and I'm still their father
and you still gonna give me your look?

24:13.870 --> 24:15.280
Yeah.

24:15.371 --> 24:17.327
You right, Antoine.

24:17.415 --> 24:21.283
I've been in the habit of doubting you
for a long time now.

24:21.377 --> 24:23.038
Maybe too long.

24:23.630 --> 24:26.292
Well, give them my love.

24:27.550 --> 24:28.960
I got to get around there and see them.

24:29.052 --> 24:31.134
Both of us.

24:31.220 --> 24:34.212
Larry been carrying all the weight, you know?

24:39.312 --> 24:40.848
Are we wrong?

24:41.397 --> 24:42.557
Oh...

24:42.649 --> 24:45.061
No, no. It ain't that cut-and-dry.

24:47.528 --> 24:49.109
You're a good woman, LaDonna.

24:49.197 --> 24:51.939
Right now, with things as they are,

24:52.033 --> 24:54.570
I reckon we're doing the best we can.

24:56.079 --> 24:57.489
You know something?

24:57.580 --> 25:00.697
I like you better now
than when we were married.

25:01.250 --> 25:03.286
-(CHUCKLES)
-Mmm-hmm.

25:03.378 --> 25:05.710
I had a growth spurt, I guess.

25:06.089 --> 25:08.626
Yeah. Yeah, you did.

25:09.592 --> 25:10.707
Thank you, Antoine.

25:12.095 --> 25:13.926
(HUMMING)

25:14.305 --> 25:16.682
Who loves you so, baby?

25:17.809 --> 25:20.767
Who needs you so bad?

25:21.604 --> 25:25.643
Who cries night till dawn?

25:26.317 --> 25:28.854
This is my favorite part right here.

25:30.279 --> 25:34.613
Is it usual to have so many deaths at the jail
in such a short period of time?

25:34.701 --> 25:37.864
It's become the norm at OPP.
I mean, we got our suicides.

25:37.954 --> 25:40.991
We got our deaths related to health issues
that were left untreated.

25:41.082 --> 25:44.415
Stabbings, inmate on inmate murders.

25:44.502 --> 25:49.747
A mental deficient got killed in a cage
when he pissed on another man's shoes.

25:49.841 --> 25:52.298
So much for Gusman's reform initiative.

25:53.469 --> 25:57.803
They spent the FEMA money on technology,
but the conditions haven't improved.

25:58.224 --> 26:02.763
In fact, the in-house deaths have risen
since the changes were implemented.

26:02.854 --> 26:05.641
I mean, what you got there
is kind of a self-assessment.

26:06.149 --> 26:09.266
I'd say so. There's a section down here,
areas for improvement,

26:09.360 --> 26:11.442
under which someone
has typed the word "none."

26:11.612 --> 26:13.819
(CHUCKLING) That ain't no surprise.

26:14.115 --> 26:16.356
Mmm. Mmm, mmm, mmm.

26:19.036 --> 26:22.073
Go easy there, Richard.
No one's gonna take it from you.

26:22.165 --> 26:24.372
Dizzy's does yardbird right.

26:24.459 --> 26:25.995
Toni Bernette.

26:26.669 --> 26:27.658
You remember who I am?

26:28.629 --> 26:29.664
Officer.

26:30.006 --> 26:31.917
How'd those Louisiana Weekly ads
work out for you?

26:32.008 --> 26:34.590
You know, your little campaign against me.

26:34.677 --> 26:36.668
You had nothing, Counselor.

26:37.722 --> 26:39.337
You had bullshit.

26:42.226 --> 26:44.137
Seems like a good guy.

26:51.527 --> 26:55.019
-So, who is this fella?
-Davis McAlary.

26:55.114 --> 26:58.277
He's kind of a community activist.
Musically involved.

26:58.367 --> 26:59.777
A little rough around the edges.

26:59.869 --> 27:02.076
-He's a DJ, I think.
-A fucking DJ?

27:02.789 --> 27:06.122
I like him. I can't help it.
And he lives in the Treme.

27:06.209 --> 27:08.200
A few blocks
from the park and the auditorium.

27:08.294 --> 27:10.535
Connected to all kinds of people
we'll need on our side.

27:12.840 --> 27:16.799
I have a small record label, Mercury Monterey.

27:16.886 --> 27:23.052
The label is very selective in terms of
the amount of artists that we handle.

27:23.851 --> 27:25.807
Very conservative in our approach.

27:26.604 --> 27:33.146
The industry is evolving,
but we're cautiously optimistic.

27:33.236 --> 27:35.022
Is there much profit
remaining in the record business?

27:35.738 --> 27:37.353
It's in a transitional period.

27:37.448 --> 27:40.531
Davis has his hands
in many different ventures.

27:40.618 --> 27:44.952
I'm a trained musicologist
with a show on WWOZ.

27:45.873 --> 27:48.364
I run musical heritage tours.

27:48.459 --> 27:54.079
I'm a local recording artist
of some modest repute.

27:54.799 --> 27:57.336
-He's diversified, boss.
-Just so.

27:58.761 --> 27:59.796
How is everything tonight, gents?

27:59.887 --> 28:01.548
-Superb.
-Good.

28:01.639 --> 28:04.255
-Holler if you need anything.
-You can burn, girl.

28:05.643 --> 28:08.885
Didn't you run for office a couple years back?

28:09.897 --> 28:14.106
I did dip my toes into that rancid water, yes.

28:14.193 --> 28:17.310
I remember your campaign platform.

28:17.405 --> 28:21.523
He was going to shame the NBA
by renaming the Hornets.

28:21.617 --> 28:22.572
What was it?

28:22.660 --> 28:25.447
The New Orleans Mormon Tabernacle Choir.

28:26.080 --> 28:29.163
To shame the Utah Jazz
until they gave us the name back.

28:29.792 --> 28:31.328
Yeah, that was mine.

28:31.419 --> 28:33.284
Also pot for potholes.

28:34.338 --> 28:37.296
Rebuilding infrastructure utilizing the...

28:41.596 --> 28:48.388
Anyway, my political aspirations
are quixotic at best.

28:48.477 --> 28:53.062
But I'm guessing you have a position on
what's gonna happen over at Armstrong Park.

28:53.149 --> 28:55.731
The idea of a National Jazz Center
has been floating...

28:55.818 --> 28:56.807
Yeah.

28:56.903 --> 29:03.320
I'd have to study the,
you know, complexities of the concept.

29:05.328 --> 29:06.443
Crunch the numbers.

29:06.537 --> 29:08.619
Look at all the implications.

29:11.834 --> 29:14.041
I will warn you that I do speak my mind.

29:14.128 --> 29:16.915
Of course. We're expecting no less.

29:22.637 --> 29:25.094
C.J. Liguori.

29:25.181 --> 29:26.261
The banker?

29:26.349 --> 29:27.338
That's me.

29:28.643 --> 29:31.055
You're one of the green dot guys.

29:31.938 --> 29:36.807
And one of the biggest
Republican fund-raisers in the state.

29:37.360 --> 29:38.691
Dude.

29:40.821 --> 29:42.982
I've been boycotting your bank
for the past 10 years.

29:43.074 --> 29:46.612
I was wondering where that $300 had gone to.

29:51.540 --> 29:57.376
(SINGING) Well, it's plain to see
You're a dangerous thing

29:57.713 --> 30:02.207
With those lips,
those hips and those eyes

30:03.094 --> 30:08.839
It's lucky for me that I like being free

30:08.933 --> 30:13.723
Or I might try and make you mine

30:14.647 --> 30:19.061
Now, I might give in and kiss you

30:20.569 --> 30:24.562
But don't plan on me staying long

30:26.283 --> 30:30.492
Now, I might give in and kiss you

30:31.664 --> 30:36.203
But tomorrow I will be gone

30:37.253 --> 30:38.413
All right.

30:38.838 --> 30:40.248
(CHEERING)

30:46.262 --> 30:47.877
So, lwent looking for you
over at the old place

30:47.972 --> 30:49.178
and you weren't there.

30:49.265 --> 30:51.677
-I saw that guy.
-Timothy Feeny?

30:51.767 --> 30:54.019
Nobody told me you left the Avenue,
but I knew.

30:54.103 --> 30:57.186
-The food wasn't right.
-Yeah, I hear they already changed the menu.

30:57.273 --> 30:59.889
N'awlins gumbo. Blackened catfish. Like that.

30:59.984 --> 31:02.350
Applebee's on the Avenue.

31:02.445 --> 31:05.152
Wasn't easy to find you, Chef.
Had to ask around.

31:05.239 --> 31:06.479
Yeah, I'm playing hard to get.

31:06.574 --> 31:08.314
Yeah, and you're good at it.

31:08.409 --> 31:11.196
-At least you could put a sign out front.
-I had one.

31:11.287 --> 31:16.077
They served me with a cease and desist on
the use of my name, so the sign came down.

31:16.167 --> 31:17.532
Old Feeny's revenge.

31:17.626 --> 31:21.790
Smegma-faced slutwhore that he is.

31:21.922 --> 31:22.911
Sorry.

31:23.382 --> 31:24.371
Can he do that?

31:24.467 --> 31:27.004
Per my contract, yes.

31:27.928 --> 31:30.715
I'm gonna try to appeal to his human side.

31:31.515 --> 31:32.630
Maybe he'll relent.

31:33.142 --> 31:34.177
Hmm.

31:34.268 --> 31:38.557
Well, you still got a customer in me.
That hanger steak I had tonight? Damn.

31:38.647 --> 31:40.183
It's the Chili rub.

31:40.274 --> 31:41.309
Delicious.

31:41.400 --> 31:44.392
-Thank you. You want another scotch?
-Please.

31:44.487 --> 31:46.148
DAVIS: Hey... Um...

31:47.656 --> 31:49.271
How do you think I did tonight?

31:50.493 --> 31:53.485
Well, Liguori's pretty particular
with who he brings into the tent.

31:54.330 --> 31:56.116
What exactly is he looking for?

31:56.207 --> 31:59.950
Citizen liaison for the Jazz Center project.

32:00.044 --> 32:02.376
Go-to guy for the Treme
and Marigny neighborhoods.

32:02.671 --> 32:04.252
Oh. So I have a shot?

32:05.299 --> 32:07.381
I'm guessing Liguori's gonna
go in a different direction.

32:07.510 --> 32:08.499
Ah.

32:12.014 --> 32:15.757
Well, it was probably
not a big payday anyway.

32:15.851 --> 32:17.352
A couple grand.

32:19.063 --> 32:20.678
It was 30 grand.

32:22.691 --> 32:25.103
-Thank you, darling.
-JANETTE: My pleasure.

32:32.868 --> 32:33.948
We have all night.

32:34.036 --> 32:36.448
Is that a promise?

32:36.539 --> 32:38.029
I'm all yours.

32:40.126 --> 32:42.242
But you're leaving in the morning.

32:42.336 --> 32:43.917
Back to Memphis.

32:44.004 --> 32:45.665
We got a studio booked.

32:45.756 --> 32:48.873
We're bringing in horns for the new record
and Jim Spake's doing the arrangements.

32:48.968 --> 32:51.880
Jim Spake.
He worked with John Hiatt, didn't he?

32:51.971 --> 32:53.882
And Cat Power and Solomon Burke.

32:54.473 --> 32:57.215
-When are you coming back?
-Soon, I hope.

32:59.728 --> 33:01.889
So, what, I'm your New Orleans girlfriend?

33:04.400 --> 33:06.186
You're my girlfriend.

33:12.700 --> 33:14.816
(POLICE CHATTER OVER RADIO)

33:18.414 --> 33:19.995
(SIREN WAILING)

33:26.463 --> 33:28.590
MAN: Her name is Cherise Laurent.

33:31.385 --> 33:33.376
Nikolich. Yeah, it's Terry.

33:33.470 --> 33:37.008
I got a body down by
the St. James AME on North Roman.

33:37.099 --> 33:40.136
Gunshot victim, a girl.
Looks like she's middle-school age.

33:40.227 --> 33:41.603
I need you down here on this.

33:41.687 --> 33:46.431
I got a couple assholes on the scene
and they're about to shit the bed.

33:46.525 --> 33:49.858
Yeah, that's right. That's right.
As soon as you can, Nik.

33:49.945 --> 33:51.105
Thanks.

33:56.994 --> 33:58.734
(SAXOPHONE PLAYING)

34:14.178 --> 34:15.964
That's Bechet, right?

34:16.055 --> 34:18.467
Yeah. Si tu vois ma mere.

34:18.557 --> 34:19.637
Nice.

34:20.809 --> 34:23.551
-Can I ask you something?
-Sure. Ask away.

34:25.439 --> 34:28.556
My manager wants me to cut my band loose.

34:28.651 --> 34:32.769
Record with studio guys in Nashville,
take a fresh crew out on tour.

34:32.863 --> 34:34.478
He wants it cleaner and prettier.

34:35.032 --> 34:37.273
-And should you go with it?
-Yeah.

34:38.035 --> 34:39.150
I don't know.

34:39.245 --> 34:42.408
That is just your second CD
on an actual label.

34:42.498 --> 34:46.537
And he'll have you touring
with some guys that are real.

34:46.627 --> 34:47.662
That's a lot to piss away.

34:48.587 --> 34:50.873
-So, would you?
-Me?

34:51.715 --> 34:53.501
I'm here.

34:53.592 --> 34:56.425
I make ends meet
by playing in about five different bands.

34:56.512 --> 34:58.468
-Come on, don't exaggerate.
-|t's true, look.

34:58.555 --> 35:00.841
Royal Roses is about to start up.

35:00.933 --> 35:04.016
Panorama. The Bechet stuff at the Hall.

35:04.103 --> 35:05.843
Why Are We Building Such a Big Ship?

35:05.938 --> 35:09.101
And, um... Oh, yeah, Rory Danger.

35:09.191 --> 35:11.056
Rory Danger?

35:11.151 --> 35:13.688
-What's that?
-You know, rockabilly.

35:13.779 --> 35:14.939
(LAUGHS)

35:15.322 --> 35:17.108
I have to see that.

35:21.537 --> 35:24.199
(PLAYING MELODY)

35:44.727 --> 35:49.892
Frankly, Toni, what's going on over at the jail
right now is not at the top of my priority list.

35:49.982 --> 35:51.688
-My plate is full.
-With what?

35:52.484 --> 35:56.523
Everything I give you,
it ends up stuck in a drawer somewhere.

35:56.613 --> 36:00.322
I gave you a witness
to the Abreu murder months ago.

36:00.409 --> 36:01.899
You know what happened?

36:01.994 --> 36:08.081
The officer that did that murder came past
my table at Dizzy's yesterday ruining lunch.

36:10.794 --> 36:12.955
Tell me what you can on the Abreu case.

36:13.422 --> 36:16.038
You know I can't comment
on an on-going investigation.

36:16.508 --> 36:19.796
(SNORTS) I give you guys gold
and you do exactly nothing.

36:19.887 --> 36:22.378
The sphinx moves faster
than you fucking feds.

36:22.473 --> 36:26.057
The material you've given us
has been extremely valuable.

36:28.645 --> 36:30.306
(SHIP HORN BLOWS)

36:33.484 --> 36:34.974
So, it's going okay?

36:35.069 --> 36:38.186
We had some bumps in the road after you left,

36:38.280 --> 36:41.522
but we've since made some accommodations
for the tourist trade.

36:42.618 --> 36:45.405
Like I said,
I'm good losing money the first year.

36:45.496 --> 36:49.034
Certainly accomplished that.
But I'm starting to see some daylight.

36:49.124 --> 36:51.331
Well, I'm glad.

36:51.418 --> 36:54.080
I'm trying to make it through
my freshman year, too.

36:54.171 --> 36:56.002
Always the toughest.

36:56.090 --> 36:57.580
Heard good things about your menu.

36:57.674 --> 37:00.165
Yeah, Jacques is doing
a nice job in the kitchen.

37:00.260 --> 37:02.637
I hope you don't mind
that I took your sous chef.

37:02.721 --> 37:05.633
Of course not. I expected he'd go with you.

37:06.433 --> 37:09.049
You must know
that it would help me immensely

37:09.144 --> 37:10.680
if I could use my name for my restaurant.

37:10.771 --> 37:12.477
I mean,
my name means something down here.

37:12.564 --> 37:13.553
As does mine.

37:14.191 --> 37:15.351
So you understand.

37:15.442 --> 37:16.727
Of course.

37:16.819 --> 37:19.526
I mean, I'm not asking you
to take my name off the Avenue.

37:19.613 --> 37:23.401
You have no legal standing to do so.
Or moral for that matter.

37:23.492 --> 37:26.279
We made a deal. I backed you to the hilt.

37:26.370 --> 37:28.827
Until it fell apart there at the end.

37:28.914 --> 37:31.280
All in all, you and I had
a pretty good relationship once.

37:31.375 --> 37:34.913
I'm asking you to remember that and
consider what losing my name does to me.

37:35.003 --> 37:38.086
You have no right to your name anywhere.

37:38.173 --> 37:39.583
I do.

37:39.675 --> 37:41.415
I told you that once before.
Did you think I was joking?

37:41.510 --> 37:44.126
-Tim!
-Read your contract.

37:44.847 --> 37:48.339
And I would suggest you have your lawyer
thoroughly read the suit.

37:49.101 --> 37:50.932
You're really gonna sue me?

37:51.937 --> 37:53.598
That interview you gave in the Pic?

37:53.689 --> 37:55.725
You said you had your own place now

37:55.816 --> 37:58.307
and you were cooking the food
you always wanted to,

37:58.402 --> 38:01.269
that Desautel's on the Avenue
was not really your thing,

38:01.363 --> 38:05.072
that you preferred fine dining
to the chain experience.

38:05.159 --> 38:08.447
That interview was read by every food blogger
and concierge in town.

38:08.537 --> 38:11.870
You disparaged my restaurant
and that impacted my livelihood.

38:11.957 --> 38:13.788
It wasn't my intention.

38:13.876 --> 38:14.865
I mean, you know what it's like.

38:14.960 --> 38:17.201
You give an interview,
sometimes the words come out wrong.

38:17.296 --> 38:20.459
You shoved it up my ass, Janette,
and Iwon't forget that.

38:20.549 --> 38:23.586
-But it's my name.
-Walk around with it.

38:23.677 --> 38:25.793
Answer to it.

38:25.888 --> 38:28.880
But you can't use it for your new restaurant.

38:32.686 --> 38:33.721
You got this, right?

38:40.903 --> 38:42.734
Can I get the check?

38:44.573 --> 38:46.529
The kids knew before me.

38:48.660 --> 38:50.821
They heard it on the street telegraph.

38:52.331 --> 38:53.537
Your students have gone home?

38:55.918 --> 39:00.537
We have an after-school band program
in this room, but I canceled it today.

39:02.883 --> 39:06.592
Iguesstheyh
bring grief counselors in tomorrow.

39:06.678 --> 39:08.794
And then we'll have a vigil.

39:10.432 --> 39:11.421
(SIGHS)

39:11.642 --> 39:13.303
That's how we do.

39:15.521 --> 39:16.636
Mr. Batiste,

39:17.231 --> 39:19.142
the girl's mother

39:19.233 --> 39:22.600
said that you came by her house
and spoke with Cherise two days ago.

39:23.779 --> 39:25.019
Yeah, that's right. I was there.

39:25.113 --> 39:26.899
Was there anything said
that we should know about?

39:29.243 --> 39:34.454
Did she identify by name the ones
who shot Deron Williams in the drive-by?

39:34.540 --> 39:36.576
She talked to your people.

39:38.043 --> 39:39.032
So why are you asking me?

39:39.127 --> 39:41.209
We're hoping she might have confided in you.

39:43.799 --> 39:47.291
She said she didn't see anyone.
Cherise told the truth.

39:49.304 --> 39:51.090
She was a good girl.

39:54.309 --> 39:56.800
She wasn't into anything wrong.

39:56.895 --> 39:58.226
Deron's older brother,

39:58.313 --> 40:01.601
he had some long-time beefs
deep in the Iberville.

40:02.985 --> 40:05.897
On the day Deron was shot, he was wearing
one of his older brother's shirts.

40:05.988 --> 40:08.900
The shooters mistook Deron for the brother.

40:10.659 --> 40:11.899
Mistook?

40:14.329 --> 40:15.364
And Cherise?

40:15.455 --> 40:19.915
We're guessing they saw her as a threat,
that she might testify as a witness.

40:24.506 --> 40:26.588
I told her to mind herself.

40:29.177 --> 40:30.132
Where did this happen?

40:30.220 --> 40:33.678
She just dropped off her kid brother
at Wicker Elementary and was walking home.

40:41.189 --> 40:43.316
Oh, that sweet girl.

40:43.817 --> 40:45.432
